  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"seraphine","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Ziggs","Seraphine"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"With Q and E online you out-range Seraphine's Q by a mile; stand behind your caster minions and roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave so it detonates on her, punishing every time she steps up to auto for a Note stack. She has to hard-shove with her passive-empowered autos to farm, which walks her into your E minefield and Short Fuse burst."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Mega Inferno Bomb reaches farther than her R, so you can body her from screens away, but she can also chunk you globally with her charm chain, hence the even skill read at 6. Land R only when her W shield is down and she's pinned by minions."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Liandry's or Ludens plus Sorc boots pushes your poke lethal; a single Q-plus-passive-auto combo takes a third of her bar before she can heal it back with W. Keep detonating the wave onto her and she cannot trade the HP back."},{"when":"Late","text":"Seraphine scales into a monster teamfight enabler with her R charm-and-shield, out-ranging your artillery zoning in 5v5 chaos, which is why the late cell flips to her. Stay maximally spaced, W-jump out of her R cone, and only commit R when her ult is on cooldown."}],"wants":{"you":["Long lanes where your Q out-ranges her Q poke","Her stepping up to auto for Note stacks into your E","W-reset spacing to dodge her charm chain"],"foe":["A grouped 5v5 where her R hits multiple targets","You mispositioning into her charm plus support CC","Sustaining your poke back with W shield between trades"]},"early":"You win levels 1-2 outright: Ziggs Q out-ranges Seraphine's Q, so throw the wave-bounce onto her whenever she moves to last-hit, and drop E on the choke so she can't dodge-farm without eating stacks.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay Ziggs-favoured; her only farm pattern is hard-shoving with empowered autos, which feeds your minefield and Short Fuse resets. She out-shields you if you trade recklessly, but pure poke on cooldown keeps you ahead.","late":"By first item your Q-and-passive combo is lethal poke, but note the late 5v5 cell belongs to Seraphine: her AoE charm and shields out-enable your single-target zoning, so hold R for when her ult is spent and never group tightly.","whys":["Ziggs Q out-ranges Seraphine's Q at level 1, letting you poke for free.","At level 2 her step-up autos for Note stacks feed your E and Short Fuse.","Level 3 gives you full Q-E poke while she must hard-shove to farm.","Levels 4-5 your minefield zones her farm and denies safe CS.","Even at 6 both ults reach globally, so it's a skill-based ult trade.","First item makes your Q-plus-auto poke lethal before her W can heal it.","Late-game 5v5 flips to Seraphine as her AoE charm and shields out-enable your zoning."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"sivir","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Sivir","Sivir"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q out-ranges Sivir's Boomerang Blade, so poke on cooldown from behind your minions and roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave onto her. Beware her E Spell Shield: bait it with an early Q, wait the split second, then follow with your real damage, because a shielded Q gives her free mana and negates your whole trade."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Mega Inferno Bomb out-ranges her kit for a global chunk, but Sivir's On the Hunt R gives her team massive engage/disengage MS, so the 6 window is skill: land your ult when her Spell Shield is down and she can't just W-shield or run through it."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is where Sivir tips ahead. Her first completed crit item plus W ricochet lets her shove you off the map, freeze you under tower, and set up all-in dives with her R engage; your poke can't keep pace with her waveclear."},{"when":"Late","text":"Sivir owns the late game: R team-wide MS engages onto your backline and her Spell Shield eats your key R or Q every fight. You must space to the absolute max, hold R until her shield pops, and rely on your support to peel her dive."}],"wants":{"you":["Baiting her E Spell Shield before your real poke lands","Long lanes to abuse your superior Q range early","Punishing her step-ups before she has waveclear items"],"foe":["A completed crit item to hard-shove and freeze you","Her R engage/disengage MS to force or dodge all-ins","Landing Spell Shield on your R or key Q every fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 favour Ziggs on raw range: your Q reaches past her Boomerang Blade, so chip her every time she moves to CS and drop E on the choke. Just respect her Spell Shield once it's up and never throw your only spell into it.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours through poke, but the game gets harder as Sivir approaches her item spike; keep baiting her E, deny her free stacks, and detonate the wave onto her before she out-scales the lane.","late":"By first item and beyond the matchup flips to Sivir: her waveclear shoves you in, her Spell Shield negates your poke and R, and her ult engages onto you in 5v5. Max spacing, hold R for a popped shield, and lean on support peel.","whys":["Ziggs Q out-ranges Sivir's Boomerang Blade at level 1 for free poke.","Level 2 lets you keep chipping her step-up CS before she has tools.","Level 3 full poke kit still beats her short-range harass.","Levels 4-5 your minefield zones her while her items aren't online yet.","At 6 it's a skill ult trade since her R MS can dodge or engage your bomb.","First item flips to Sivir as her crit and W ricochet shove and freeze you.","Late-game Sivir dominates with R engage and Spell Shield eating your key spells."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"smolder","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Smolder is a stack-hungry scaling carry who is weak and short-ranged until his Q ramps, and your Q out-ranges everything he has early. Poke him relentlessly from behind your minions and roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave onto him so he can't safely farm the Q stacks he desperately needs."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Mega Inferno Bomb out-ranges his kit and threatens him from screens away while his R is a slow skillshot he must aim; drop E under him so he can't sidestep and body him whenever he steps up to stack, keeping the level-6 cell yours."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your Liandry's/Ludens poke spike lands well before his Q reaches its late breakpoints; keep detonating the wave onto him and deny stacks so his scaling never comes online. A support with CC turns your poke into a kill before he can kite."},{"when":"Late","text":"Even scaled, Smolder must stand and channel to output damage while your artillery zones from max range; you retain the cell because your R and Q reach his backline and your W resets space away from his dragon R. Stay spaced and punish every stack attempt."}],"wants":{"you":["Denying his early Q stacks with wave-bounce poke","Long lanes to abuse your range while he's weak","E minefield to stop him sidestepping and farming safely"],"foe":["Free farm to ramp his Q stacks uncontested","Reaching his late Q breakpoints unbothered","Sustaining through your poke to out-scale you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are firmly Ziggs: Smolder is helpless and short-ranged before his Q stacks, so your longer-range Q chips him for free and E locks the choke. Every last-hit he goes for is a poke opportunity.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours; his only path is farming stacks, and your wave-bounce plus minefield denies exactly that. Keep him low and starved so his scaling curve never catches up.","late":"You hold even the item and 2+ cells because a stacked Smolder still must channel and aim to deal damage while you zone from artillery range; space to the max, save W to dodge his R, and punish each stack attempt.","whys":["Smolder is weak and short-ranged at level 1 while your Q pokes freely.","Level 2 keeps you ahead as he can't contest your range or stack safely.","Level 3 full poke kit denies the stacks his scaling depends on.","Levels 4-5 your minefield starves his farm and keeps him low.","At 6 your global R out-ranges his aimed ult, so you body him first.","First-item poke spike lands before his Q breakpoints, keeping you ahead.","Late-game you still zone from max range while he must channel to output."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"swain","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Ziggs","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Your Q out-ranges Swain's Q Death's Hand cone by a wide margin, so poke from behind your minions and never walk into his E Nevermove range. Roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave onto him and drop E where he'd stand to pull; if he lands E-into-W you can W-jump out before the root connects for the full combo."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Swain's R Demonic Ascension only heals if he's close, but his soul-fragment sustain makes the 6 window skill-based; kite backward, refuse to feed his passive stacks, and use your Mega Inferno Bomb to chunk him from outside his E-pull range so he can't leech HP back."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Your poke item comes online and Swain relies on landing E to do anything; deny that one root and he's a stationary sustain target for your Q-plus-passive combo. Keep spacing so his only engage is a telegraphed E you can sidestep or W away from."},{"when":"Late","text":"You hold the late cell because Swain in botlane must get on top of you to ramp his R, and your artillery zoning plus W repositioning keeps him at bay; save W to break his E root, poke his soul stacks off, and never group inside his ult radius."}],"wants":{"you":["Max range to abuse your Q over his Death's Hand cone","W-jumping out of his E Nevermove root","Poking his soul-fragment sustain off before he heals"],"foe":["Landing E Nevermove to root you into his W and combo","Getting close enough to leech HP with his R","You clumping so his ult and pull hit multiple targets"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Ziggs: your Q vastly out-ranges Swain's short cone, so chip him whenever he steps to CS and stay well outside E range. He can't threaten you without landing a root you're not near yet.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours through poke and spacing; his whole kit hinges on the E-W root combo, so pre-position to W-jump it and detonate the wave onto him. Deny his sustain stacks and he can't trade back.","late":"You keep the item and 2+ cells because Swain must close distance to ramp his R heal, and your zoning, poke, and W escape keep him out; hold W for his E, chip his soul stacks, and refuse to group inside his ult.","whys":["Ziggs Q hugely out-ranges Swain's Death's Hand cone at level 1.","Level 2 keeps you safe outside E range while you poke his CS.","Level 3 full poke kit punishes him whenever he steps up.","Levels 4-5 your spacing and minefield deny his E-W root setups.","At 6 it's skill: his R heals only if he closes, so kiting decides it.","First item lets your poke punish his reliance on landing a single root.","Late-game your zoning and W escape keep him from ramping his ult on you."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"tristana","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Tristana","Tristana","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early Tristana is short-ranged and can't reach you, so your Q out-ranges her autos and E; poke from behind minions and roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave onto her. Drop E where she'd land her W Rocket Jump so a gap-close eats the minefield, and keep her low before her range and reset spike come online."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This flips to Tristana: her level-6 R Buster Shot is a point-blank knockback nuke, and if she W-jumps onto you her passive range plus E Explosive Charge detonation bursts you before your Satchel can reset space. Ward her jump angle and hold W to reposition the instant she leaps."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Tristana stays ahead here; her first crit item plus E-stack detonation and W-reset-on-kill make her all-in lethal, and she can dive your poke position and reset out. Keep E charged under you, save W as a panic reposition, and never sit at low HP within her jump range."},{"when":"Late","text":"You reclaim the late cell: in 5v5 Tristana must jump into your team to reset, and your artillery zoning plus W disengage punish her the moment she commits without a target to kill. Space to the max, drop E on her landing spot, and let your support CC her mid-jump."}],"wants":{"you":["Abusing your range before she hits levels and items","E under you to punish her W Rocket Jump gap-close","Late 5v5s where her jump-in over-commits with no reset"],"foe":["Level 6 W-jump plus R Buster Shot all-in burst","A crit item and E detonation to blow you up on the dive","Resetting her W on a kill to snowball the lane"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Ziggs: Tristana is at her shortest range and can't contest your Q, so poke her off every CS and set E on her likely jump path. Build a lead now because her mid-lane spike is coming.","mid":"The lane flips at 6: her W Rocket Jump plus R knockback and E-stack detonation out-burst you in an all-in, and her item spike keeps her ahead through first item. Play safe, keep E charged, and hold W purely to survive her jump.","late":"You take back the 2+ cell because a committed Tristana jump in teamfights over-extends into your zoning and W disengage; space to the max, drop E on her landing, and let support peel so her all-in finds no reset.","whys":["Tristana is shortest-ranged at level 1 while your Q pokes her freely.","Level 2 keeps you ahead before her jump and burst come online.","Level 3 full poke kit still out-reaches her early harass.","Levels 4-5 your minefield zones her before her power spike hits.","At 6 Tristana flips ahead with W-jump plus R Buster Shot all-in burst.","First item keeps her ahead via crit, E detonation, and W kill-reset.","Late 5v5 returns to you as her committed jump over-extends into your zoning."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"twitch","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Twitch","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Twitch is a weak, short-ranged laner before items, so your Q out-ranges him completely; poke him off every CS and roll Bouncing Bomb through the wave. The real threat is his Q Ambush stealth ganks, so drop E on the flanks and river brush and detonate your minefield where he'd sneak in to punish the approach."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"The 6 window is skill: your Mega Inferno Bomb can body him from range, but his R Spray and Pray plus support setup lets him unstealth and shred you and your ADC in seconds. Keep vision on his stealth angle and pre-place E so he can't walk in unpunished."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Twitch tips ahead here: his first crit item makes his R spread-shot lethal, and a stealth all-in with support CC can delete your position before you reset with W. Ward obsessively, hold W to disengage the instant he appears, and never sit low in unwarded lane."},{"when":"Late","text":"You reclaim the late cell because in 5v5 Twitch must unstealth into range to fire his R, and your artillery zoning plus W disengage punish his approach; hold vision, drop E on his flank path, and let your support CC him the moment he reveals so he never gets the spread-shot off."}],"wants":{"you":["Poking him off CS while he's weak pre-items","E on flanks and brush to punish his Q Ambush approach","Vision to pre-empt his stealth all-in with your W ready"],"foe":["A crit item to make his R Spray and Pray lethal","Stealth flanks with support CC to delete your position","Catching you low and unwarded for a reset all-in"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are Ziggs: Twitch is at his weakest and can't contest your Q range, so chip him off farm and set E toward the brush so his stealth approach eats the minefield. Deny him early and his scaling stalls.","mid":"Levels 3-6 stay yours on raw poke, though 6 is skill as his R plus a stealth setup can burst you; keep vision on his flank angle, pre-place E, and hold W to punish or escape his unstealth.","late":"First item flips to Twitch as his crit-empowered R and stealth all-in out-threaten you, but you take back the 2+ cell: in teamfights he must reveal into your zoning to fire, so hold W, ward his path, and let support CC him mid-approach.","whys":["Twitch is weakest and short-ranged at level 1 while your Q pokes freely.","Level 2 keeps you ahead before his stealth and items come online.","Level 3 full poke kit out-reaches his early harass and punishes CS.","Levels 4-5 your minefield zones his flanks before his spike hits.","At 6 it's skill: his R and stealth setup can burst you if vision slips.","First item flips to Twitch as crit makes his R Spray and Pray lethal.","Late 5v5 returns to you since he must reveal into your zoning to fire R."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"varus","win":["Skill","Skill","Skill","Ziggs","Varus","Varus","Varus"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Once you have all three abilities you out-range Varus's auto-poke: sit at max Q range, bounce Bouncing Bomb through the caster minions onto him, and drop Hexplosive Minefield on the chokes so he can't walk up to last-hit without eating stacks. Respect that a fully-charged Piercing Arrow out-ranges your Q, so never stand still in a straight line while his W Blighted Quiver stacks are ticking."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Varus flips the lane at 6: his Chain of Corruption (R) roots you and chains to your support, and with W stacks his combo bursts you before you can Satchel out. Keep W Satchel Charge up as an escape, hug your minions so the R travels less distance, and don't shove blindly into a warded bush where his root guarantees a kill."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On one item Varus's Blighted Quiver empowered autos and Piercing Arrow poke out-trade your single-target Q if he lands his kit; his sustained DPS and R engage make the mid-game his window. Play for zone control with E minefields rather than face-checking, and only step up when his ult is down."},{"when":"Late","text":"In 5v5 Varus scales as a hyper-carry with on-hit or lethality builds and his R starts fights; your job is artillery from the back line. Fire Q and R over walls into the grouped enemy, place E on the choke they must cross, and never be the front-most target when his Chain of Corruption is up."}],"wants":{"you":["A short lane state so you can Q-poke from max range without his all-in","Your support landing CC to punish him while his R is on cooldown","Grouped enemies you can hit with R and E from safety in teamfights"],"foe":["W Blighted Quiver stacks ticking on you so his empowered autos and Q shred","His R Chain of Corruption up to root you and your support into an all-in","A straight-line, minion-light lane where his charged Piercing Arrow out-ranges you"]},"early":"Levels 1-2 are a skill lane: neither of you has a real threat, so focus on clean last-hits and don't walk into charged Piercing Arrow poke in the open. Match his auto-harass with a poke Q only when a bounce lands cleanly through the minions.","mid":"By level 3 you have the range edge and can bully with Q bounces and E zoning, but the moment Varus hits 6 his Chain of Corruption plus W stacks turn the lane against you. Keep Satchel Charge saved as an escape and never overstay in a bush when his ult is up.","late":"On items Varus is the stronger duelist and fight-starter, so don't try to win a straight trade; instead play as backline artillery, poke with Q/R over walls, and let his R be the thing you dodge or Satchel away from before your team collapses.","whys":["Level 1 is even because neither Ziggs nor Varus has a kill threat and it's pure last-hitting.","Level 2 stays skill-based as both trade only chip damage with no all-in available yet.","Level 3 is even: Ziggs gains range but Varus's charged Piercing Arrow and W stacks keep trades close.","Ziggs is favoured at 4-5 once his full poke kit out-ranges Varus's auto-harass before Varus's ult comes online.","At 6 Varus's Chain of Corruption root plus W-stacked burst gives him the all-in kill Ziggs can't answer.","On first item Varus's empowered autos and Piercing Arrow poke out-DPS Ziggs's single-target damage.","With two-plus items Varus scales into a hyper-carry whose R starts fights, keeping the edge his."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"vayne","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Vayne","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Vayne is one of the weakest early ADCs and you hard-outrange her: her Silver Bolts and Tumble need auto range, so sit at max Q and bounce Bouncing Bomb onto her every time she steps to CS. Blanket the wave and her tumble spots with Hexplosive Minefield so she can't Q-reposition to farm without taking chip, and keep her permanently under her tower."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Your Mega Inferno Bomb lets you execute her from screens away, and she has no ult-based escape from it since Final Hour only gives stealth on Tumble, not range. Poke her low with Q, then finish with R as she backs; respect that if she gets on top of you with Condemn (E) stun against a wall she can still burst you, so hold Satchel Charge to knock yourself away."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Vayne's spike: with a first item and Final Hour her Silver Bolts true damage and Tumble resets let her all-in and shred you if she closes the gap. Keep maximum spacing, use E minefields as a physical wall between you and her, and never get cornered where Condemn can stun you against terrain."},{"when":"Late","text":"Vayne is a premier hyper-carry late, but in 5v5 you're artillery that never lets her reach you: fire Q and R from the back, wall off dive paths with E, and rely on your team's peel. If she blinks in with Tumble, Satchel Charge yourself out of her true-damage range and reset the fight from distance."}],"wants":{"you":["Max-range poke so you punish her short auto range before she itemizes","Her forced to farm inside your Hexplosive Minefield under tower","A level-6 R pick on her while she's low and has no escape from artillery"],"foe":["A first item plus Final Hour to enable her Tumble-reset all-in","Terrain nearby so Condemn can stun you against a wall","A late-game teamfight where she gets on your backline with Silver Bolts true damage"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are heavily yours: Vayne has almost no early poke or wave presence, so zone her off CS with Q bounces and E minefields and deny her the farm she desperately needs. Keep her under tower and starve her early item timings before she can spike.","mid":"Through level 6 you stay ahead because you out-range her and your R executes her from afar; keep poking her low and finishing with Mega Inferno Bomb. The only danger is letting her Condemn-stun you into a wall, so always keep Satchel Charge ready as a get-off-me tool.","late":"On her first item plus Final Hour Vayne finally out-duels you if she closes, but by two-plus items the lane reverts to your favour in teamfights as pure backline artillery. Space her out, wall dive paths with E, and never be the target she can Tumble onto.","whys":["Level 1 favours Ziggs since Vayne has no early damage and Ziggs pressures the wave immediately.","Level 2 stays Ziggs's: his Q range dwarfs Vayne's short auto and Tumble range.","Level 3 is Ziggs-favoured as his full kit zones Vayne off CS with poke and minefields.","At 4-5 Ziggs keeps starving Vayne's farm before she can reach any item spike.","At 6 Ziggs's R executes a low Vayne from range she cannot escape or answer.","On first item Vayne's Final Hour and Silver Bolts true damage let her all-in and out-duel Ziggs.","With two-plus items Ziggs reclaims the edge as safe artillery that never lets Vayne reach him."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"veigar","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Skill","Veigar","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"You win the poke war early: your Bouncing Bomb comes out faster and bounces around minions, while Veigar's Baleful Strike (Q) is a slow, dodgeable line he needs to farm stacks with. Sit at max range, deny his Q last-hits by clearing the caster minions with your own Q, and drop Hexplosive Minefield on his step-up spots so he can't safely stack. Never stand in his Dark Matter (W) landing zone."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"This is the coin-flip level: Veigar's Event Horizon (E) cage plus Primordial Burst (R) can one-shot you if he lands the stun, but you have Satchel Charge to reposition out of the cage edge and R to poke him first. Play around the E cooldown — after he throws it, step up freely; while it's up, hug your minions and never walk in a straight line toward him."},{"when":"1st item","text":"On one item Veigar's AP spikes hard and his E-into-R combo becomes lethal; a single landed Event Horizon likely kills you. This is his window, so respect the cage: keep Satchel Charge ready to flick yourself out, hold flash for the all-in, and poke only when his E is on cooldown."},{"when":"Late","text":"Veigar scales infinitely with stacks, but he's immobile and telegraphed. In 5v5 you're artillery from the very back: never be within Event Horizon range of the fight, poke him and his team with Q/R over walls, and force him to blow E on a frontliner. If he cages you, Satchel out of the ring before his R lands."}],"wants":{"you":["A poke lane where your faster Q out-harasses his slow Baleful Strike","Denying his Q last-hits so his stack scaling falls behind","Playing around his Event Horizon cooldown to step up safely"],"foe":["A landed Event Horizon cage to lock in his Primordial Burst one-shot","First-item AP so his E-into-R combo becomes instantly lethal","You walking in a straight line into Dark Matter or the cage edge"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are yours: your Q is a faster, safer poke than Veigar's Baleful Strike, and you can deny the minion kills he needs to stack AP. Zone him with Q and E, keep him off farm, and make his scaling start behind.","mid":"Level 6 is a genuine coin-flip — his Event Horizon plus Primordial Burst one-shots you on a landed stun, but you out-poke him and can Satchel out of the cage. Track his E cooldown religiously and only commit when it's down.","late":"Once Veigar hits his first item the all-in swings to him, but with two-plus items and proper spacing you reclaim the edge as backline artillery he can't reach. Stay outside cage range, poke over walls, and Satchel yourself free the instant he lands E.","whys":["Level 1 favours Ziggs as his quick Bouncing Bomb out-pokes Veigar's slow Baleful Strike.","Level 2 stays Ziggs's since he can deny Veigar's Q stacks and win the harass.","Level 3 is Ziggs-favoured: full kit lets him zone Veigar off farm and control the wave.","At 4-5 Ziggs keeps starving Veigar's stacks before Veigar's combo comes online.","Level 6 is even because Veigar's cage-plus-R one-shots on a hit but Ziggs can Satchel out and out-poke.","On first item Veigar's AP spike makes a landed Event Horizon combo lethal, giving him the edge.","With two-plus items Ziggs's safe artillery range beats immobile Veigar who can't reach him."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"xayah","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Xayah","Xayah","Xayah"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Early you out-range Xayah hard: her Double Daggers (Q) and feather-drop harass need auto range, so poke her with Bouncing Bomb from max distance and drop Hexplosive Minefield where she wants to pick up her feathers with Bladecaller (E). Deny her the passive plumage stacks by keeping her out of auto range, and never let her cheap max-range feather-recall root chip you for free."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"Xayah's Featherstorm (R) makes her untargetable and drops a wall of blades that can root you and your support, flipping any trade in her favour. Keep spacing so her E feather-line doesn't catch you, hold Satchel Charge to escape the root setup, and don't over-poke into a fight where her R negates your damage and sets up the all-in."},{"when":"1st item","text":"Xayah's power comes online at one item: her Bladecaller root plus Featherstorm becomes a genuine all-in that out-trades you, and her clean-up DPS on the plumage is high. This is her window — play back, use E minefields as a zone wall, and only poke when her R and a feather-line aren't threatening a root."},{"when":"Late","text":"Late, Xayah is a self-peeling teamfight monster: Featherstorm dodges your Q and R while making her untargetable, and her feather rows root multiple carries. You're artillery that must respect her all-in — poke from the very back, never stand in a feather line, and Satchel yourself out if she flanks. Her R timing dictates when your team can commit."}],"wants":{"you":["Max-range poke before Xayah reaches auto range to harass","Her feather-pickup and CS spots blanketed with Hexplosive Minefield","Forcing her Featherstorm early so your team can commit after"],"foe":["First-item Bladecaller-into-Featherstorm all-in that out-trades you","A feather line landing so her E root locks you for the follow-up","R untargetability to dodge your Q and R in the fight"]},"early":"Levels 1-4 are yours: Xayah has to be in auto range to build plumage and drop feathers, so poke her with Q from max distance and zone her feather spots with E. Deny her stacks, keep her off CS, and press your range advantage before she itemizes.","mid":"From level 5 onward Xayah's Bladecaller root and Featherstorm shift the lane against you — her E can lock you into an all-in and her R negates your poke. Keep tight spacing, save Satchel Charge for the root, and stop over-committing into her feather setups.","late":"On items Xayah out-duels you and her R makes her a self-peeling carry, so don't contest her directly. Play pure backline artillery, poke over walls, avoid every feather line, and let her burn Featherstorm before your team engages.","whys":["Level 1 favours Ziggs since his Q out-ranges Xayah's auto-range harass.","Level 2 stays Ziggs's as he pokes freely before Xayah can build plumage stacks.","Level 3 is Ziggs-favoured: full kit zones her feather spots and denies CS.","At 4-5 Ziggs keeps the range edge and starves Xayah before her spike.","At 6 Xayah's Featherstorm untargetability and feather root flip trades her way.","On first item Xayah's Bladecaller-into-R all-in out-trades Ziggs decisively.","With two-plus items Xayah scales into a self-peeling carry whose R dodges Ziggs's artillery."]},
  {"a":"ziggs_bot","b":"zeri","win":["Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Ziggs","Zeri","Ziggs"],"spikes":[{"when":"Lvl 3-5","text":"Zeri is weak and short-ranged early: her Burst Fire (Q) is an auto-attack-range mini-cannon, so you comfortably out-poke her with Bouncing Bomb from distance. Blanket her CS approach with Hexplosive Minefield so she can't walk up to farm, and punish every time she steps into Q range. Note her W Ultrashock Laser is a skillshot slow — don't stand in a straight line, but otherwise bully her off the wave."},{"when":"Lvl 6","text":"You stay ahead at 6: your Mega Inferno Bomb pokes and can finish her, and she has no ult-based escape from artillery — Lightning Crash (R) is a scaling steroid, not a get-out button. Keep spacing so her W slow doesn't set up a gank, poke her low with Q, and hold Satchel Charge in case she E-dashes over terrain onto you."},{"when":"1st item","text":"This is Zeri's spike: her first item plus Lightning Crash lets her ramp move speed and shred, turning her into a slippery skirmisher who out-DPSes you if she gets going. This single window is hers — play back, wall her dash paths with E minefields, and don't feed her R stacks by fighting into a low-percent trade."},{"when":"Late","text":"Zeri is a mobile hyper-carry late, but she's squishy and reliant on ramping R uptime. In 5v5 you're artillery from the back: poke her and her team with Q/R before she gets rolling, and place E on the choke she must dash through. If she E's onto you, Satchel Charge yourself away and reset — deny her the sustained DPS window."}],"wants":{"you":["Max-range poke to punish Zeri's short auto-range Q early","Her farm spots blanketed with Hexplosive Minefield to deny CS","Killing her before her first item and Lightning Crash come online"],"foe":["First item plus Lightning Crash to ramp move speed and shred","A prolonged fight so her R stacks and DPS snowball","Her E dash over terrain closing the gap onto you"]},"early":"Levels 1-5 are firmly yours: Zeri's Burst Fire is auto-range while your Q pokes from afar, so zone her off CS with bombs and minefields and keep her farm starved. Deny the early gold she needs and don't let her free-hit you with W slows into a gank.","mid":"You hold the edge through level 6 because you out-range her and your R can finish a low Zeri, who has no escape ult against artillery. Keep spacing, poke her down, and save Satchel Charge for her E dash so she can't stick to you.","late":"Zeri's first item plus Lightning Crash is her one strong window where she out-DPSes you, but by two-plus items disciplined spacing reclaims the matchup. Play backline artillery, wall her dash paths with E, and Satchel away the moment she jumps you.","whys":["Level 1 favours Ziggs since his Q out-ranges Zeri's short auto-range Burst Fire.","Level 2 stays Ziggs's as he pokes freely while Zeri must be in auto range to farm.","Level 3 is Ziggs-favoured: full kit zones Zeri off CS and controls the wave.","At 4-5 Ziggs keeps starving Zeri's farm before her item spike lands.","At 6 Ziggs stays ahead as his R finishes a low Zeri who has no escape ult.","On first item Zeri's Lightning Crash and move-speed ramp let her out-DPS and out-skirmish Ziggs.","With two-plus items Ziggs's safe artillery spacing beats squishy, R-reliant Zeri again."]}
